subSubSection.paragraph:
Teeth (
Fig. 4
) moderately large, conical. Intermaxillary in two transverse rows, separated from maxillary and vomerine teeth, mostly excluded from closed mouth. Maxillary and mandibular teeth in bands, wider anteriorly, roughly in four to five rows, narrower posteriorly, in one to two rows; outermost teeth larger than innermost. Vomerine tooth patch longer than broad, reaches to level of posterior nostril; teeth conical, shorter than those of intermaxillary, about equal size, in three to four rows anteriorly and one to two rows posteriorly.
